news.title: Hema Malini sells two apartments for ₹12.50 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Veteran actress Hema Malini has recently sold two apartments in Mumbai's Oberoi Springs for a combined ₹12.50 crore. Each apartment, boasting a carpet area of 847 sq ft, was sold for ₹6.25 crore, inclusive of one car parking space.

news.title: Nuvoco Vistas to invest ₹200 crore to add four MMTPA capacity
news.para: Nuvoco Vistas Corp plans a ₹200 crore investment to expand cement grinding capacity by four MMTPA at the Arasmeta plant, alongside upgrades at other facilities. These strategic moves, including the Vadraj Cement acquisition, aim to solidify their leadership in the East and increase market share in the West and North.

news.title: Panchkula: Only 24,000 among one lakh assessees pay property tax
news.para: Panchkula's Municipal Corporation faces a significant shortfall in property tax collection, with only a fraction of registered assessees paying by the deadline. This has resulted in a massive gap between the expected Rs 155 crore and the actual Rs 6.62 crore received. Poor enforcement and substantial dues from government departments have financially strained the civic body, impacting infrastructure and services.

news.title: Karnataka: Property registration fee hike adds to inventory worries amid tepid June quarter sales
news.para: Karnataka's decision to double property registration fees to 2% is anticipated to negatively impact Bengaluru's housing market, already strained by affordability issues. Experts caution that this increase in transaction costs could weaken buyer sentiment, particularly affecting the mid- and affordable segments.

news.title: Apple expands Hyderabad presence with fresh lease of 64,000 sq ft at WaveRock
news.para: Apple India is growing in Hyderabad. It has leased more office space in WaveRock. The new lease starts in July 2025. Apple will pay monthly rent for the space. This expansion shows Apple's focus on India. Hyderabad is important for Apple's technology work. WaveRock is a popular place for big companies. Apple's move strengthens its presence in India.

news.title: Lucknow development body announces plot draw for Anant Nagar
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority will conduct a lottery from September 8-10 at Indira Gandhi Pratishthan for 332 residential plots in Anant Nagar Housing Scheme. The lottery, streamed live on LDA's YouTube channel, follows 8,568 online applications received in the second phase. The Anant Nagar scheme, spanning 785 acres, aims to accommodate 1.

news.title: Odisha gets seven new municipalities, 16 NACs, to improve civic amenities
news.para: Chief Minister Mohan Charan Majhi announced the creation of seven new municipalities and sixteen notified area councils to improve civic amenities and strengthen urban local bodies. He mandated that all urban areas must be pothole-free and have closed drains by April 2026.

news.title: Police investigate Mumbai land scam involving forged documents and illegal sale of BMC property
news.para: Mumbai police are investigating a land scam in Kandivli, where heirs of a developer allegedly forged documents to reclaim land surrendered to the BMC for additional FSI. The accused, including the original landowner and the developer, purportedly sold the BMC land to third parties using a fraudulent power of attorney.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Karimadam colony housing complex opened with 128 flats
news.para: Thiruvananthapuram's Karimadom Colony Housing Complex, featuring 128 flats, was inaugurated, marking progress in providing affordable housing. Built at a cost of Rs 27 crore, this is the first phase of a 200-home initiative. The city corporation actively implements housing projects, having completed thousands of homes, with 700 more under construction.

news.title: UK lenders approved most mortgages in six months in July
news.para: British lenders approved the highest number of mortgages in July since January, signaling a stabilization in the housing market following tax break volatility. Approvals exceeded expectations, with 65,352 mortgages signed off. Despite this positive trend, Nationwide Building Society reported an unexpected drop in house prices for August. Consumer borrowing also saw a significant increase, rising by 7.

news.title: Brookprop Management Services pays ₹20.47 lakh to settle REIT norms violation case with Sebi
news.para: Brookprop Management Services settled a case with Sebi for Rs 20.47 lakh concerning alleged violations of REIT norms. Sebi's show cause notice claimed the entity used borrowed funds to distribute Net Distributable Cash Flow. The settlement allows Brookprop to resolve the proceedings without admitting or denying any findings.

news.title: Tathastu Realty to invest ₹200 crore on high-street retail project in Haryana's Rewari
news.para: Tathastu Realty is set to invest Rs 200 crore in developing 'Swarnim', a six-acre high-street retail project in Rewari, Haryana. The project, featuring 1,200 shops priced at Rs 14,000 per sq ft, anticipates a total sales realization of approximately Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Puravankara’s subsidiary secures redevelopment project in Malabar Hill
news.para: Puravankara, via Purva Blue Agate, has secured redevelopment rights for a 1.43-acre residential society in Mumbai's Malabar Hill, offering a development potential of 0.7 million sq ft. This acquisition boosts Puravankara's Mumbai redevelopment portfolio to 4.25 million sq ft, with a potential GDV of ₹10,500 crore and an estimated revenue of ₹2,700 crore.

news.title: Supertech gives possession of 6,000 flats in last three years; 15,000 buyers still stuck
news.para: Supertech Ltd, undergoing insolvency, has delivered 6,121 apartments across 16 projects in the last three years. The company aims to deliver 1,000 more flats in the next three months. A resolution plan involving Apex Heights, with a Rs 500 crore investment, awaits Supreme Court approval to complete the remaining 15,000 units within two years.

news.title: Excel Infra to invest ₹250 crore to develop new project in Mumbai
news.para: Excel Infra Construction is set to invest Rs 250 crore in a new luxury residential project, 'Bellissima,' at Bandra Reclamation in Mumbai. The 33-story tower will feature 96 units, with apartments priced at Rs 51,500 per square foot. The company anticipates generating Rs 400 crore in revenue from the project, funded through equity and an Alternative Investment Fund.

news.title: Builder held in Thane for selling flats constructed using fake permits
news.para: Umrao Singh Prithviraj Ostwal, director of Ostwal Builders, is now in police custody. He allegedly defrauded apartment buyers in Thane. Ostwal used fake construction permits and maps. He built extra units in Mira Bhayander's Ostwal Paradise Building No. 6. Buyers lost crores of rupees. Police found 13 other cases against him. Authorities advise verifying permits before property purchase.

news.title: Maharashtra likely to finalise discounted property tax rate for merged areas this week
news.para: The Maharashtra government and Pune Municipal Corporation officials will meet to decide on property tax rates for 32 merged areas. Residents want discounted rates, citing high taxes and lack of amenities. The state had directed PMC to charge lower taxes, but officials sought clarity. A previous meeting with Deputy CM Ajit Pawar led to this upcoming discussion.

news.title: Nashik civic body launches rebate scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: The Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) has launched an amnesty scheme starting Sept 1 for property tax defaulters, aiming to recover a portion of the outstanding Rs784 crore, including Rs327 crore in penalties. The scheme offers a 95% waiver on penalties for payments made by Oct 31 and 85% in November.

news.title: SC upholds refusal to stay termination of salt pan land lease due to non-use in Mumbai
news.para: The Supreme Court upheld the Bombay High Court's decision to partially lift a stay on the termination of a lease for 150 acres of salt pan land, part of a larger 782-acre property.

news.title: OSB's director faces FIR for fund misuse & licence violations in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana authorities have filed an FIR against Ocean Seven Buildtech and its director, Swaraj Singh, for financial fraud and license violations in affordable housing projects. The company allegedly collected payments without completing construction, leading to stalled projects and financial distress for buyers.
